---
import LegalLayout from '../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { company } from '../../data/company';

const ALTS = { en: '/legal/terms', hu: '/hu/aszf', de: '/de/agb' };
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of service for Hyperscales — a browser-based tycoon game operated by Polyák Csaba e.v. (PromNET) from Hungary."
  lang="en"
  alternates={ALTS}
  updated="2026-05-14"
>
  <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    Plain-English terms for the Hyperscales browser game (open beta).
  </p>
  <div class="lang-row">
    <span class="active">English</span>
    <a href="/hu/aszf">Magyar</a>
    <a href="/de/agb">Deutsch</a>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    Hyperscales (<a href="https://hyperscales.app">hyperscales.app</a>) is operated by
    <strong>{company.name}</strong>, a Hungarian sole proprietor, brand <strong>{company.brand}</strong>,
    registered at {company.address.full}. Tax number: <code>{company.taxNumber}</code>.
    Contact: <a href={`mailto:${company.email}`}>{company.email}</a>. Full details on the
    <a href="/legal/imprint">imprint page</a>. Hyperscales is part of the {company.parent} family
    of products (<a href={company.parentUrl}>{company.parentUrl}</a>).
  </p>

  <h2>2. What Hyperscales is</h2>
  <p>
    Hyperscales is a browser-based simulation game where you build a fictional hosting company
    and interact with AI-generated non-player characters. It is provided <strong>"as-is"</strong>
    during open beta. Features may change, break, or disappear without notice.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Who can play</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You must be at least <strong>16 years old</strong> (or the GDPR digital-consent age in your country).</li>
    <li>You agree not to use the game for anything illegal under Hungarian or EU law.</li>
    <li>One human, one account. No bot accounts, no farming. We may rate-limit or close accounts at our discretion.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Your account</h2>
  <p>
    You're responsible for the security of your password. If you use cross-brand single sign-on
    (SSO) via {company.parent}, the same account terms apply.
    Tell us at <a href={`mailto:${company.abuseEmail}`}>{company.abuseEmail}</a> if you suspect
    unauthorized access.
  </p>

  <h2>5. AI-generated content</h2>
  <p>
    Customer messages, tickets, NPC dialogue and similar in-game text are generated by large
    language models (LLMs). They are <strong>fictional</strong> and may produce inaccurate, weird,
    or offensive output. We don't endorse it. If you see something that crosses a line
    (illegal content, harassment, CSAM-adjacent material), report it to
    <a href={`mailto:${company.abuseEmail}`}>{company.abuseEmail}</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can plug in your own LLM API key. In that case the LLM provider's terms apply to those
    calls — we just forward them.
  </p>

  <h2>6. User-generated content</h2>
  <p>
    Names, company titles, public profile text and any other content you submit must not be
    illegal, defamatory, sexual content involving minors, or copyrighted material you don't own.
    We may remove content and/or close accounts that violate this without notice.
  </p>
  <p>
    You retain ownership of what you create. You grant us a worldwide, royalty-free license to
    host, display and process it as needed to run the game.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Payments</h2>
  <p>
    The game is <strong>free during open beta</strong>. We may add paid plans later — separate
    terms and a cancellation flow will apply, and we'll notify you in advance. You are not
    auto-enrolled into anything paid.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Service availability</h2>
  <p>
    We aim for high uptime but make no SLA during beta. We may schedule maintenance, throttle
    abusive traffic, or shut down regions without prior notice. Your save data is stored in
    Cloudflare D1 (EU region by default) and is best-effort durable, not guaranteed.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Termination</h2>
  <p>
    You can stop playing and ask us to delete your account anytime — email
    <a href={`mailto:${company.privacyEmail}`}>{company.privacyEmail}</a> with the subject
    "delete my account". We respond within 30 days. We may suspend or terminate accounts that
    abuse the service, violate these terms, or threaten the safety of other users.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent allowed by Hungarian and EU law, Hyperscales is provided without
    warranty of any kind. We are not liable for lost gameplay progress, lost revenue from
    third-party LLM costs, or other indirect damages. Mandatory consumer-protection rules under
    Hungarian law (e.g. for natural persons acting as consumers) are not affected.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these terms. Material changes will be announced in the app and reflected by
    a new "Last updated" date below. Continued play after a change means you accept the new
    version. If you don't, stop playing and ask us to delete your account.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Disputes &amp; governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of Hungary. Disputes go to the competent Hungarian
    court at our registered seat. EU consumers may also use the European Commission's
    <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Online Dispute Resolution platform</a>.
    Consumers in Hungary may contact the local Conciliation Body (Békéltető Testület).
  </p>

  <h2>13. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Anything unclear, anything weird, anything to dispute:
    <a href={`mailto:${company.legalEmail}`}>{company.legalEmail}</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
